pageDataArray[25] = [0,'Carriage Mechanism','carriagemechanism','The major components of the carriage (CR) mechanism are the CR Unit (A), CR Encoder (B), CR Scale (C), CR Motor (D), CR Belt (E). Since the carriage mechanism moves the Printhead to the left or right to do printing, this is a critical mechanism that impacts printing quality. The CR Unit (A) is placed and held on the Main Frame (F). By rotating the CR Motor (D), CR Unit (A) fixed to the CR Timing Belt (E) moves left and right to perform printing. The position and speed of the CR Unit (A) are always monitored by the CR Encoder (B)and CR Scale (C), and the CR Motor (D) is controlled based on information from the CR Encoder (B).','themajorcomponentsofthecarriage(cr)mechanismarethecrunit(a),crencoder(b),crscale(c),crmotor(d),crbelt(e).sincethecarriagemechanismmovestheprintheadtotheleftorrighttodoprinting,thisisacriticalmechanismthatimpactsprintingquality.thecrunit(a)isplacedandheldonthemainframe(f).byrotatingthecrmotor(d),crunit(a)fixedtothecrtimingbelt(e)movesleftandrighttoperformprinting.thepositionandspeedofthecrunit(a)arealwaysmonitoredbythecrencoder(b)andcrscale(c),andthecrmotor(d)iscontrolledbasedoninformationfromthecrencoder(b).','40535447.html'];
pageDataArray[26] = [0,'Paper Feed Mechanism','paperfeedmechanism','Each mechanism related to Paper Loading/Feeding Mechanism are driven by the PF Motor (B) which is controlled by the PF Encoder (A). The driving force of the PF motor (B) is transmitted to the PF roller (D)/EJ roller (E) via the PF belt (C). The Pickup Roller (F) and Intermediate Roller (H) of the Rear Cover Unit (G) are driven via the PF roller (D). Paper Feed Path Paper is fed from the cassette as shown below. Paper loaded into the Paper Cassette (A) is fed to the Intermediate Roller (C) of the Rear Cover Unit by the Pick Up Roller Assy (B), and then arrives at the PE Sensor (D) position. Next, printing on the paper is performed while the paper is being fed by the PF Roller (E) and EJ Roller (F), and ejected to the Stacker (G). Auto Duplex Printing When printing on one side is finished, the printer waits for the ink on the one side to dry keeping the paper nipped between the PF Roller (A) and Driven Roller (B). After a predetermined drying time has passed, the PF Roller (A) and EJ Roller (C) are rotated in the reverse direction to pull the paper inside the Duplex unit. When the leading edge of the paper is detected by the PE Sensor (D), skew is corrected, and then printing on the back side is performed.','eachmechanismrelatedtopaperloading/feedingmechanismaredrivenbythepfmotor(b)whichiscontrolledbythepfencoder(a).thedrivingforceofthepfmotor(b)istransmittedtothepfroller(d)/ejroller(e)viathepfbelt(c).thepickuproller(f)andintermediateroller(h)oftherearcoverunit(g)aredrivenviathepfroller(d).paperfeedpathpaperisfedfromthecassetteasshownbelow.paperloadedintothepapercassette(a)isfedtotheintermediateroller(c)oftherearcoverunitbythepickuprollerassy(b),andthenarrivesatthepesensor(d)position.next,printingonthepaperisperformedwhilethepaperisbeingfedbythepfroller(e)andejroller(f),andejectedtothestacker(g).autoduplexprintingwhenprintingononesideisfinished,theprinterwaitsfortheinkontheonesidetodrykeepingthepapernippedbetweenthepfroller(a)anddrivenroller(b).afterapredetermineddryingtimehaspassed,thepfroller(a)andejroller(c)arerotatedinthereversedirectiontopullthepaperinsidetheduplexunit.whentheleadingedgeofthepaperisdetectedbythepesensor(d),skewiscorrected,andthenprintingonthebacksideisperformed.','40535414.html'];
pageDataArray[27] = [0,'Functions Using the CIS Module','functionsusingthecismodule','CIS Module The printer is equipped with the CIS Module (A), which is located facing the paper feed path right after the Rear Cover Unit (B). During scanning by the CIS module (A), the Flap (C) is raised and paper is fed to the paper feed path right above the Rear Cover Unit (B) and scanning is performed by the CIS module (A). The Flap (C) is driven by the PF motor. Function Following functions are performed by reading printed contents and paper with the CIS Module. Nozzle Detection Function As one of the auto nozzle check functions, it detects nozzle clogging and ink droplet impact misalignment (droplet curving) by reading the printed nozzle check pattern with the CIS Module. Condition Performed when nozzle detection function is enabled by the user with maintenance tool. Timing Depending on the setting of maintenance tool (Performed before printing or by each number of paper set) Operation Print the check pattern on photo paper. Rotate the PF Roller in reverse direction to pull the check pattern into the printer, and read the printed check pattern with the CIS Module. The printer analyzes the read image and checks the nozzle clogging state. If nozzle is clogged, appropriate cleaning or nozzle clogging correction setting is performed according to the setting of maintenance tool.','cismoduletheprinterisequippedwiththecismodule(a),whichislocatedfacingthepaperfeedpathrightaftertherearcoverunit(b).duringscanningbythecismodule(a),theflap(c)israisedandpaperisfedtothepaperfeedpathrightabovetherearcoverunit(b)andscanningisperformedbythecismodule(a).theflap(c)isdrivenbythepfmotor.functionfollowingfunctionsareperformedbyreadingprintedcontentsandpaperwiththecismodule.nozzledetectionfunctionasoneoftheautonozzlecheckfunctions,itdetectsnozzlecloggingandinkdropletimpactmisalignment(dropletcurving)byreadingtheprintednozzlecheckpatternwiththecismodule.conditionperformedwhennozzledetectionfunctionisenabledbytheuserwithmaintenancetool.timingdependingonthesettingofmaintenancetool(performedbeforeprintingorbyeachnumberofpaperset)operationprintthecheckpatternonphotopaper.rotatethepfrollerinreversedirectiontopullthecheckpatternintotheprinter,andreadtheprintedcheckpatternwiththecismodule.theprinteranalyzesthereadimageandchecksthenozzlecloggingstate.ifnozzleisclogged,appropriatecleaningornozzlecloggingcorrectionsettingisperformedaccordingtothesettingofmaintenancetool.','40535405.html'];
