pageDataArray[324] = [0,'Moving','moving','Caution / 注意 When lifting the printer, work in a posture that does not damage your body. When lifting the printer, place your hands at the locations indicated in the following figure from the front. The printer may fall if you lift it by holding other areas, and your fingers could be caught which may cause an injury. Do not move the printer while internal components are pulled out. Dropping this could result in injury. Check Point / チェックポイント When moving or transporting this product, do not tilt it, stand it, or turn it upside down. Ink may leak. Moving method This section explains how to move the printer over short distances, such as to a different location within the same building. Check Point / チェックポイント When moving the printer, do not slide it out; instead ensure it is lifted. Doing so may cause a malfunction to occur. Preparations for moving Make the following preparations in advance before moving the printer. Remove all paper from the paper cassette. Turn off the printer and remove all cables. Work after moving. After moving, prior to use check that there is no clogging in the Print Heads.','caution/注意whenliftingtheprinter,workinaposturethatdoesnotdamageyourbody.whenliftingtheprinter,placeyourhandsatthelocationsindicatedinthefollowingfigurefromthefront.theprintermayfallifyouliftitbyholdingotherareas,andyourfingerscouldbecaughtwhichmaycauseaninjury.donotmovetheprinterwhileinternalcomponentsarepulledout.droppingthiscouldresultininjury.checkpoint/チェックポイントwhenmovingortransportingthisproduct,donottiltit,standit,orturnitupsidedown.inkmayleak.movingmethodthissectionexplainshowtomovetheprinterovershortdistances,suchastoadifferentlocationwithinthesamebuilding.checkpoint/チェックポイントwhenmovingtheprinter,donotslideitout;insteadensureitislifted.doingsomaycauseamalfunctiontooccur.preparationsformovingmakethefollowingpreparationsinadvancebeforemovingtheprinter.removeallpaperfromthepapercassette.turnofftheprinterandremoveallcables.workaftermoving.aftermoving,priortousecheckthatthereisnocloggingintheprintheads.','48433897.html'];
pageDataArray[325] = [0,'Transport','transport','Caution / 注意 When lifting the printer, work in a posture that does not damage your body. When lifting the printer, place your hands at the locations indicated in the following figure from the front. The printer may fall if you lift it by holding other areas, and your fingers could be caught which may cause an injury. Do not move the printer while internal components are pulled out. Dropping this could result in injury. Preparation for transport Open the internal cover, and set the transport lock to the transport position as in the figure. Setting the transport lock to the transport position prevents ink leakage during transport. Use commercially available tape or similar to secure the Print Head so that it does not move. Securely apply commercially available tape (A) or similar to the positioning line (B) so that the Maintenance Box does not move during transport thus resulting in recognition errors. Check that the ink tank cap is firmly closed. Place in the transport bag included with the printer, and close the bag.','caution/注意whenliftingtheprinter,workinaposturethatdoesnotdamageyourbody.whenliftingtheprinter,placeyourhandsatthelocationsindicatedinthefollowingfigurefromthefront.theprintermayfallifyouliftitbyholdingotherareas,andyourfingerscouldbecaughtwhichmaycauseaninjury.donotmovetheprinterwhileinternalcomponentsarepulledout.droppingthiscouldresultininjury.preparationfortransportopentheinternalcover,andsetthetransportlocktothetransportpositionasinthefigure.settingthetransportlocktothetransportpositionpreventsinkleakageduringtransport.usecommerciallyavailabletapeorsimilartosecuretheprintheadsothatitdoesnotmove.securelyapplycommerciallyavailabletape(a)orsimilartothepositioningline(b)sothatthemaintenanceboxdoesnotmoveduringtransportthusresultinginrecognitionerrors.checkthattheinktankcapisfirmlyclosed.placeinthetransportbagincludedwiththeprinter,andclosethebag.','48433882.html'];
pageDataArray[326] = [0,'Transporting Ink Bottles','transportinginkbottles','Refer to the following points when transporting Ink Bottles. Place in a sealable bag before transport. During transport, do not tilt or subject to sudden changes in temperature. Ink may leak even if the cap of the Ink Bottle is securely tightened. Do not place open bottles in the same box as the printer.','refertothefollowingpointswhentransportinginkbottles.placeinasealablebagbeforetransport.duringtransport,donottiltorsubjecttosuddenchangesintemperature.inkmayleakevenifthecapoftheinkbottleissecurelytightened.donotplaceopenbottlesinthesameboxastheprinter.','48433898.html'];
